emononen*`|`*Erno Mononen*`|`*2010-08-12T13:17:14Z*`|`*I suppose the problem may be in how the EL refactoring uses the Java APIs since the issue manifests itself only there, but I&amp;apos;m not sure what should be done differently. Basically EL refactoring gets a TPH from the refactoring context:

handle = refactoring.getRefactoringSource().lookup(TreePathHandle.class);

then gets a CompilationInfo as follows:

JavaSource source = JavaSource.create(cpInfo, new FileObject[]{handle.getFileObject()});
